headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 30 points and nine rebounds, Bradley Beal added 29 points and the Washington Wizards took advantage of Joel Embiid's absence for a 121-111 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis, Beal lead Wizards over Embiid-less 76ers, 121-111

headlines.description: — Darius Garland missed everything while sitting on the bench, but mostly the joy of playing and winning.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garland scores 29 in return, Cavs edge Celtics 114-113 in OT

headlines.description: — Tyler Herro's vision is fine again.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro's 3 with 1.8 seconds left lifts Heat by Kings, 110-107

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray scored a career-high 36 points and the Atlanta Hawks overcame a 23-point deficit to beat the New York Knicks 112-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray has career-high 36, Hawks rally past Knicks, 112-99

headlines.description: — On an off night for two of Chicago's biggest stars, Javonte Green and the rest of the Bulls picked up the slack.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green scores 17 as Bulls cruise past Hornets 106-88

headlines.description: — Paul George scored 28 points, Marcus Morris added 21 and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Houston Rockets 109-101 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George leads Clippers over Rockets 109-101 with Leonard out

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 32 points and 12 rebounds and the Milwaukee Bucks matched a franchise record with their seventh straight win to open the season, beating the Detroit Pistons 116-91 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks match franchise record with 7th win to open season

events.name: Toronto Raptors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam had 22 points, 11 assists and 10 rebounds in just 28 minutes, and the Toronto Raptors beat depleted San Antonio 143-100 on Wednesday night, the Spurs’ worst home loss in franchise history.
headlines.shortLinkText: Siakam, Trent help Raptors overwhelm depleted Spurs, 143-100

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic scored 33 points, his seventh consecutive game of at least 30 to begin the season, reserve Christian Wood added 17 of his 21 in the second half and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Utah Jazz 103-100 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Another 30-point game by Doncic leads Mavericks past Jazz

events.name: Memphis Grizzlies at Portland Trail Blazers
New Orleans Pelicans at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Matt Ryan hit a tying 3-pointer at the regulation buzzer, Lonnie Walker made a key 3-pointer in overtime while scoring 28 points, and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the New Orleans Pelicans 120-117 Wednesday night for their second straight victory...
headlines.shortLinkText: Ryan forces OT, Lakers rally for 120-117 win over Pelicans
